<<setup-step "2" "Create GitHub Personal Access Token" """
1. Go to GitHub ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Developer settings ‚Üí [Personal access tokens](https://github.com/settings/tokens)
2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
3. Set expiration and select scopes:
   - ‚úÖ `repo` (Full control of private repositories) - **This is the only scope needed**
4. Copy the token (save it securely - you won't see it again!)
""">>

<<setup-step "3" "Create Cloudflare Function" """
Create a file at `functions/save.js` in your repository root.

**Quick Setup**: Copy the complete function code from the `demo/functions/save.js` file in the plugin repository: https://github.com/BenSweaterVest/tiddlywiki-cloudflare-saver

The function includes:
* üîê Password authentication and rate limiting
* ‚úÖ Content validation and size limits
